    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-beef-mince-ragu-with-herby-greek-cheese-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the potatoes are cooking, peel and finely dice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced red onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-beef-mince-ragu-with-herby-greek-cheese-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further</p><p>Add the <strong>beef mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-beef-mince-ragu-with-herby-greek-cheese-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the mince is browning, top, tail and chop the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Once the mince has browned, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>courgette</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min further or until the courgette has started to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-beef-mince-ragu-with-herby-greek-cheese-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the<strong> beef stock mix </strong>and the<strong> harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>harissa stock</strong></p><p>Once the courgette has softened, add the <strong>harissa stock</strong> and <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and cook for 10-12 min or until the sauce has thickened to a bolognese-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>harissa beef mince rag\u00f9</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-beef-mince-ragu-with-herby-greek-cheese-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the beef rag\u00f9 is cooking, strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p><p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the <strong>stalks</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-beef-mince-ragu-with-herby-greek-cheese-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat<strong> </strong>with a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Crumble in <strong>half</strong> of the<strong> Greek cheese</strong> and add <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>and<strong> mint </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Mash until smooth then taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt </strong>if needed \u2013 this is your <strong>herby Greek cheese mash</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-beef-mince-ragu-with-herby-greek-cheese-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>herby Greek cheese mash</strong> on a plate, make a well in the centre and fill with the <strong>harissa beef mince rag\u00f9</strong></p><p>Crumble over the<strong> remaining Greek cheese </strong>and sprinkle over the<strong> remaining chopped parsley </strong>and<strong> mint</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
